In EBNF (Extended Backus-Naur Form), this could look as follows:
<pre>
expr -> term {[ ('+' | '-') term ]}
term -> factor {[ ('*' | '/') factor ]}
factor -> base {[ '^' exponent ]}
base -> '(' expr ')' | identifier | number
exponent -> '(' expr ')' | identifier | number

</pre>


https://stackoverflow.com/questions/17162919/unambiguous-grammar-for-exponentiation-operation
